description:
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Commissioning Group lies within the boundaries of the East Riding of Yorkshire covering 1000 square miles of rural, urban and coastal geography and is responsible for the commissioning of healthcare services for the majority, but not all, of the East Riding of Yorkshire population (the Pocklington population are the responsibility of the Vale of York CCG). As such we work closely with our neighbouring CCGs to promote consistency of commissioning with our major provider organisations and with East Riding of Yorkshire Council to ensure that we are jointly commissioning and transforming services to improve the overall health and wellbeing of our population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CCG consists of 36 GP Practices who have come together to jointly commission services for their patient populations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to use Clinical Commissioning to drive the transformation of local services to better meet the needs of our resident population. This will be achieved whilst continuing to work within the national operational guidance which underpin the wider aspirations, and delivery, of the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vision and Values &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CCG, along with the Health and Wellbeing Board, remains focused upon its vision to provide ‘&lt;strong&gt;Better care, more locally, within budget through transformation’ &lt;/strong&gt;with the underlying premise that &lt;strong&gt;‘Everyone needs to do something different’ &lt;/strong&gt;to improve health and healthcare, including patients, carers, clinicians, wider public, healthcare professionals and social care professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vision is supported by our organisational values of &lt;strong&gt;effective partnership working, ensuring everyone counts, providing quality services, effective leadership and integrity, &lt;/strong&gt;ensuring we&lt;strong&gt; involve &lt;/strong&gt;and continue to&lt;strong&gt; improve &lt;/strong&gt;in the way we behave as an organisation to achieve our vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced and motivated experienced Programme Manager to join Humber, Coast and Vale Cancer Alliance. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working as part of the senior leadership team, the post holder will help manage and support the delivery of transformation work within the Alliance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cancer Alliances have a key role in delivering the NHS Long Term Plan, which identifies two clear targets; by 2027 there will be 55,000 more cancer survivors and three quarters of cancers will be diagnosed at an early stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This new role that has been created to ensure the Alliance has oversight of its programmes of work and can clearly demonstrate the progress that is being made with regards to early diagnosis of cancer and support for people living with and beyond a diagnosis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be skilled in leading teams to high performance and should have experience of managing multiple programmes of delivery; including the development strong governance systems and clear reporting skills to ensure the Board has full sight with regards to the progress we are making. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will have the ability to work effectively with a wide range of stakeholders, including health professionals, senior managers, people affected by cancer, and third sector organisation’s. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are at an exciting point in our journey and this is a fantastic opportunity to join the Cancer Alliance team and influence how we deliver improved cancer outcomes for the Humber, Coast and Vale population.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Yvonne Elliott, Managing Director, HCV CA ON 07557104454.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
